---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import { GITHUB_URL } from "../config";
---

<LegalLayout title="Privacy Policy" lastUpdated="July 22, 2026">
  <p>
    This is the privacy policy for LasagnaFi, a personal finance app made by
    <strong>SuperCoolLabs LLC</strong>. It explains what happens to your data.
  </p>
  <p>
    The short version: we collect the data we need to run the app for you, we
    never sell it, and we don't run ad trackers. The longer version is below.
  </p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <p>Here's the data we hold, and why:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Your account details.</strong> Your email address, and your name
      if you give it to us. This is how you sign in and how we reach you.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Your financial data.</strong> When you connect a bank, brokerage,
      or credit card through Plaid (see below), we store the account balances,
      transactions, and holdings that come back so we can show you your money
      and give you insights. You can also type in accounts by hand.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>What you tell the app.</strong> Your goals, plans, and the
      questions you ask in chat.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The services we rely on</h2>
  <p>
    We use a small number of trusted software services to make the app work, and
    we only pass each one the data it needs to do its job. These include, but are
    not limited to, the following, and this may not be a comprehensive list, as
    the services we use can change over time:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Plaid</strong> connects your financial accounts. When you link an
      account, Plaid securely handles your bank login and sends us your balances
      and transactions. We never see your bank password. That stays between you
      and Plaid. Connections are read-only: we can see your accounts, but we
      can't move money.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>WorkOS</strong> handles sign-in and sends the one-time login codes
      to your email.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Stripe</strong> processes payments if you subscribe to a paid plan.
      Your card details go straight to Stripe, and we never store your card
      number.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>AI models (via OpenRouter).</strong> The insights and chat answers
      are generated by AI. Before anything is sent to the AI, your identity is
      stripped out and replaced with anonymous tokens. The model sees numbers and
      patterns, never your name, your bank, or your account numbers.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    These are processors we depend on to run the service, not partners we sell
    your information to. Each of them (Plaid, WorkOS, Stripe, OpenRouter, and the
    others we use) is its own company with its own privacy policy governing the
    data it processes on our behalf. We do <strong>not</strong> sell your data to
    anyone, and we do not share it with advertisers.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics and tracking</h2>
  <p>
    We do not currently use any third-party analytics, advertising pixels, or
    cross-site tracking. There is no Google Analytics, no Facebook pixel, no ad
    retargeting. We don't follow you around the internet.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    We use a single cookie to keep you signed in. That's it, with no tracking or
    advertising cookies.
  </p>

  <h2>How your data is kept safe</h2>
  <p>
    Your data is encrypted in transit, and access is limited to what's needed to
    run the service. Your connection to your banks through Plaid is read-only, so
    no one can move your money through LasagnaFi.
  </p>

  <h2>How long we keep your data</h2>
  <p>
    We keep your data for as long as you have an account, so the app can keep
    working for you. When you delete your account from Settings, we remove your
    personal and financial data from our systems. Some information may stay in
    backups for a short while before it rolls off, and we may keep the minimum we
    need to meet a legal or accounting obligation. The services we rely on, like
    Plaid and Stripe, keep their own records under their own policies.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    LasagnaFi is meant for adults managing their own money. It is not directed to
    children, and you must be at least 18 to use it, in line with our
    <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>. We don't knowingly collect data from
    anyone under 18 (or under 13 in any case). If you believe a child has given us
    data, email us and we'll delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>No liability</h2>
  <p>
    We work hard to protect your data, but no system is perfectly secure, so we
    provide the service "as is" and can't guarantee it will never be breached. To
    the maximum extent permitted by law, SuperCoolLabs LLC is not liable for any
    damages arising from a security incident or from your use of the app. This is
    also covered in our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Your privacy rights</h2>
  <p>
    You're in control of your data, and you can exercise these rights yourself:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>See and correct your data.</strong> Most of what we hold is visible
      in the app, and you can edit or update it from Settings. If you need
      something you can't see there, email us and we'll help.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Delete your account.</strong> You can delete your account at any
      time from Settings. This removes your data from our systems.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Disconnect accounts.</strong> You can unlink any connected
      financial account whenever you want.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    These rights are open to everyone, and they cover the access, correction, and
    deletion rights that laws like California's give residents there. We don't
    sell your data or share it for advertising, so there's nothing to opt out of
    on that front. You won't be treated differently for using any of these
    rights. If you'd like help, email us at
    <a href="mailto:dheeraj@supercoollabs.com">dheeraj@supercoollabs.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Prefer to keep everything yourself?</h2>
  <p>
    LasagnaFi is open source. If you'd rather your data never leave your own
    server, you can
    <a href={GITHUB_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">self-host</a>
    the whole thing.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we make meaningful changes, we'll update the "Last updated" date at the
    top of this page.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about your privacy? Email us at
    <a href="mailto:dheeraj@supercoollabs.com">dheeraj@supercoollabs.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
